------------------------------------------------------------------------
Heritage
------------------------------------------------------------------------
C⏚ ("C-Ground") is the continuation of the Synflow Cx toolchain, originally
developed by Synflow (until 2021) and maintained and evolved by Neosyn since
2024. Portions of this codebase originate from that work.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scope
------------------------------------------------------------------------
This repository contains the C⏚ language frontend and the Verilog code
generator only. The fast (bytecode) simulator, the VHDL backend, the license/
activation tooling, and the production IP cores are part of the commercial
Neosyn distribution and are not included here. See https://neosyn.io/open.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party components
------------------------------------------------------------------------
This software builds on the Eclipse Xtext / Xtend / EMF frameworks and the
Eclipse LSP4J library, each distributed under the Eclipse Public License.
Build-time and runtime dependencies retain their respective licenses.
